{
  "background": "A consumer advocacy group wants to determine whether there is a difference between the proportions of the two leading automobile models that need major repairs (more than $500) within 2 years of their purchase. A sample of 400 two-year owners of model 1 and a sample of 500 two-year owners of model 2 are contacted. The numbers of owners who report that their cars needed major repairs within the first 2 years are 53 and 78, respectively.",
  "task": [
    {
      "query": "What are the null and alternative hypotheses for testing whether there is a difference between the proportions of the two automobile models needing major repairs?",
      "answer": "$$ H_0: \\left(p_1 - p_2\\right) = 0 $$ $$ H_a: \\left(p_1 - p_2\\right) \\neq 0 $$"
    },
    {
      "query": "What is the test statistic and the rejection region for the hypothesis test at $\\alpha = 0.10$?",
      "answer": "Test statistic: $$ z = \\frac{\\left(\\hat{p}_1 - \\hat{p}_2\\right) - 0}{\\sigma_{\\left(\\hat{p}_1 - \\hat{p}_2\\right)}} $$ Rejection region: $$ |z| > z_{\\alpha / 2} = z_{0.05} = 1.645 $$"
    },
    {
      "query": "How do you calculate the sample proportions of owners who needed major car repairs for each model?",
      "answer": "$$ \\hat{p}_1 = \\frac{x_1}{n_1} = \\frac{53}{400} = 0.1325 $$ $$ \\hat{p}_2 = \\frac{x_2}{n_2} = \\frac{78}{500} = 0.1560 $$"
    },
    {
      "query": "How do you calculate the pooled sample proportion $\\hat{p}$, and why is it used?",
      "answer": "$$ \\hat{p} = \\frac{x_1 + x_2}{n_1 + n_2} = \\frac{53 + 78}{400 + 500} = 0.1456 $$ $\\hat{p}$ is a weighted average of $\\hat{p}_1$ and $\\hat{p}_2$, with more weight given to the larger sample size."
    },
    {
      "query": "What is the computed value of the test statistic $z$?",
      "answer": "$$ z = \\frac{0.1325 - 0.1560}{\\sqrt{(0.1456)(0.8544)\\left(\\frac{1}{400} + \\frac{1}{500}\\right)}} = \\frac{-0.0235}{0.0237} = -0.99 $$"
    },
    {
      "query": "What conclusion can be drawn from the hypothesis test at $\\alpha = 0.10$?",
      "answer": "The samples provide insufficient evidence at $\\alpha = 0.10$ to detect a difference between the proportions of the two models that needed repairs within 2 years."
    }
  ],
